</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Main interest(s)</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="History" title="History">History</a> and <a href="Geography" title="Geography">Geography</a></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Notable work(s)</th>
<td class="" style="">
<p><small>Muruj adh-dhahab wa ma'adin al-jawhar (“<a href="The_Meadows_of_Gold" title="The Meadows of Gold">The Meadows of Gold</a> and Mines of Gems”)</small></p>
<small>at-Tanbih wa-l-ishraf ("Notification and Review")</small></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Abu al-Hasan Ali ibn al-Husayn ibn Ali al-Mas'udi</b> (in <a href="Arabic_language" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a> أبو الحسن علي بن الحسين بن علي المسعودي transl: <b><span title="ar ALA transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">Abu al-Ḥasan ʿAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn ibn ʿAlī al-Masʿūdī</span>)</b> (born c. 896, <a href="Baghdad" title="Baghdad">Baghdad</a>, died September 956, <a href="Cairo" title="Cairo">Cairo</a>, <a href="Egypt" title="Egypt">Egypt</a>), was an <a href="Historiography_of_early_Islam" title="Historiography of early Islam">Arab historian</a> and <a href="Geographer" title="Geographer">geographer</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Al-Masudi (in <a href="Arabic_language" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a> المسعودي) was one of the first to combine <a href="History" title="History">history</a> and scientific <a href="Geography" title="Geography">geography</a> in a large-scale work, <i><a href="Muruj_adh-dhahab_wa_ma'adin_al-jawhar" title="Muruj adh-dhahab wa ma'adin al-jawhar" class="mw-redirect">Muruj adh-dhahab wa ma'adin al-jawhar</a></i> (<a href="Arabic_language" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" xml:lang="ar">مروج الذهب ومعادن الجواهر</span>‎ translated <i><a href="The_Meadows_of_Gold" title="The Meadows of Gold">The Meadows of Gold and Mines of Gems</a></i>), a world history.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
