<li id="cite_note-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://209.85.122.83/2505/29/0/p1006798/Tashreeh.pdf">http://209.85.122.83/2505/29/0/p1006798/Tashreeh.pdf</a></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Al-Masudi&action=edit&section=10.php.html" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><span class="citation book">"Masʿūdī, Abuʾul-ḤasanʿAlī Ibn al-Ḥusayn Ibn ʿAlī al-". <i><a href="Dictionary_of_Scientific_Biography" title="Dictionary of Scientific Biography">Dictionary of Scientific Biography</a></i>. New York: Charles Scribner's Sons. 1970–80. <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="Special_BookSources/0684101149" title="Special:BookSources/0684101149">0684101149</a>.</span></li>
<li>Ahmad A. M. Shboul, <i>Al-Mas'udi and His World</i>, Ithaca Press, London, 1979</li>
<li>Mas'udi, <i>The Meadows of Gold, The Abbasids</i>, transl. Paul Lunde and Caroline Stone, Kegan Paul, London and New York, 1989</li>
<li>Haywood. John A. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/368842/al-Masudi">Mas'udi, al-</a>." Encyclopædia Britannica. 2006. Encyclopædia Britannica Online. 7 December 2006.</li>
<li>"Masūdī, al-." Encyclopædia Britannica. Encyclopædia Britannica 2007 Ultimate Reference Suite. Chicago: Encyclopædia Britannica, 2006.</li>
</ul>
